values:
Ok, remember last time i talked about Lenny and Josie?  Ok this story involves them.  ok, so a few weeks ago, i told lenny to ask josie to prom.  i hounded him about it, my boyfriend hounded lenny about it, a few of my friends hounded him about it, josie's protective older brother hounded him about it.  lenny's not a relationship guy, he doesn't fall for girls easily, and he's pretty shy.   so he FINALLY works up the courage to ask her to prom.  she's THRILLED, cause she'd been looking forward to it for like 3 weeks.  so prom comes and he and my boyfriend pick me and josie up, go to lenny's house to take pictures (lenny's filthy, horribly rich), then to the restaurant, then to prom.  when we get there, josie goes off with her bitchy grade-older-than-us friend (who just recently decided she wasn't mad at josie for no reason and is a total party girl flirt and doesn't seem to like me) and hangs out with her and her group for the whole night.  Well this girl, lets call her susan, has a two-years-older-than-us friend named todd.  todd is your all american boy.  he plays football, he's got short blonde-brown hair, tan, always nice to everyone, perfect white smile, wants to join the army.  two days after the prom, TODAY, josie tells me she likes todd more than lenny. BAM.  i'm devestated.  poor lenny is all i can think.  he really started to like her and she oesn't like him back cause she'd rather go out with mr. marine.  but then again she doesn't know him.  i wish she knew him.  he's like the second most amazing guy i've ever met (no one can top the boyfriend) and he deserves to be with a girl he likes, not to meantion a great girl like josie.  and might i mention, todd is 2 years older than her and treats her like a little sister.  her brother is already protective enough, he would eat her soul for dinner if she went out with him. 


i hate highschool. 


i hate drama. 



someone tell me what to do.

i used to be overflowing with love for everyone, especially my boyfriend.  now i'm pissed non stop at nothing.  its like i'll be talking to someone and they'll say ANYTHING even SLIGHTLY against what i want or say and i'll start to hate them.  and somewhere in my mind, i ask 'what is wrong with me?  why am i suddenly a bitch?'  i've found myself starting to dislike my jimi.  which makes me sad.


although.  i'm not all out of my mind, he has changed, or else i have.  i find him very immature now, when i used to never have a problem with it.  I find myself avoiding him when usually i would never do that.  but as soon as i'm away from him, i'm hitting myself, because i still do love him.  i still do think he's amazing.  i still want to be with him.  I still miss him.



but i've found myself so hateful lately.  hating on everyone.  its venomous.

i would like it to stop.

it's  three in the morning.

i'm becoming obsessive, i think.

over what, i don't know.

but i imagine i'll stay up a while longer.



maybe until 5.

i need to find something to rant on.

inspriational blockage.  sucks.  i dont ever get inspired.  nothing is ever new, nothing is ever original, nothing is ever earth-shattering.  nothing is worth it.  except for those few times when it is.  but i dont write very well lately anyways.  i have these great ideas, but crafting words together in an eloquent and not-chunky way is so difficult!  my writing is always very awkward.  i hate it.

oh well.

hello 3 am.

goodbye sleep.

ONE)  They are so goddamn immature.  I am so sick of the constant penis jokes and the constant fart jokes.  Seriously, that shit got old so fucking long ago.  Grow the hell up.

TWO) They don't respect me.  Hitting on me left and right, even though I have a boyfriend and everyone knows i have a boyfriend.  Making sexist jokes left and right about my place being in the kitchen or cleaning or some bullshit.  And I can't count how many times guys have taken pens out my back pocket or commented on my cellphone in my back pocket or commenting on my necklace that hangs right in front of my cleavage or slapped my ass or stuck their finger down my cleavage.  I am so bloody sick of it.  ITS NOT FUNNY, I DON'T FIND IT ATTRACTIVE.  GROW THE FUCK UP. 

THREE)  When i make a fuss about these things, what do i get told? "Lighten up man.  Just go with the flow."  No, i won't go with the flow, I don't like this constant bullshit.  Would they tell a black guy to lighten up if they were making lynching and slavery jokes to lighten up?  No.  But they tell me because femminists are whiny bitches, I guess.


Whatever.  i'm just waiting until they grow up and become civilized people.  because these guys are great guys just need some maturing to do, cause damn.


--KT

Hi everyone.  Just ignore this post from now on.  Don't click the LJ-cut.  It's just random nonesense that you should only want t know if you're an insomniac who wants to listen to someone whine incessantly.

 

 

 I have no talents. 

 

I'm not good at drawing, I'm not good at writing, I'm not good at poetry, I'm not good at writing essays, I'm not good at debating, I'm not outstandingly smart and I'm not athletic.  If you can think of one thing that I'm good at, YIM me or e-mail me or comment here or something.  There is not one thing that i can think of that I'm good at.  Nothing.

 

On a lighter note, I'm moving.  Pretty cool.  Though I'll miss my RL friends like mad.  Oh well.  I'll have my horses.  And my cousin's horses.  Yeah.  other than that, I'll have a bigger house, a pool, a bigger lot, gerbils (they are the cutest rodents alive), and I'll be around people like me.  I'm usually very stong opinioned to mix, everyone come together and be humans, friends, whatever, but this is too much.  It's too LIBERAL here and I'm beginning to feel my own identity as a white, Christian, Conservative Republican slipping away.  I'm ACTUALLY thinking more about animals than people!  It's starting to scare me.  Badly.  So, in that aspect I'm glad to move. 

 

Also, I've got a new site, Athena's also an admin, called Limickry's School For Those Who Are Particularly Magical.  It's a school for magical people, like hogwarts, except like half the population of this world is magical and the non-magical people know about the magi and everythings cool.  I'm explaining it horribly.  Oh yeah, it's a roleplaying site.

 

Anyways, there's not much more going on with me.  Bye. 

 

Seph

Hey all.  

Guess what?

Go on, guess.

No, that's not it.

I've been off the computer for like 2 weeks.  Scary, I know.

Anyhow, Never fly America West.  In order to get to New Mexico, we have to take a connecting flight rom Pheonix.  So We fly to phoenix.  All is cool.  But I'm hungry.  Well, guess what, all the restaurants close at 9.  We had like 20 minutes between flights and we had to go OUTSIDE security to find a bag of chips for my dinner.  So we go back to the gate and there's a huge crowd behind the counter so my dad asks what was going on and appearently our flight had been cancelled and we couldn't get on another one until 3 days later.  So we said 'to hell with that!' (not in those exact words) and spent the night in a hotel on America West's money and had to drive, 5 HOURS, to Albuquerque.  Well thjat was all fine and grand.

Then we went to Texas.  It was okay.  Blah.  My cousin broke up with her little boyfriend because his mother was talking shit about my uncle, her dad, saying he was on drugs or something.  But this time she seemed almost human.  Oh well.  It won't last for long.

I spent New Years with my parents in a hotel room.  At midnight, I called Athena, who was in a different year than me, which sounds really odd, no?  then I went to sleep for 3 and a half hours and woke up to get on a plane that was supposed to leave at 6 AM, but they had forgotten to check the bloody engines. --;  So they had to replace it because the pilot tried to start it and it was being retarded and wouldn't start.  So we didn't get off of the ground until an HOUR after we were supposed to.  So, naturally, we miss our flight.  --; The only good thing was that we got to fly first class.  Which was sweet. 

I have a feeling it's going to be a very bad year.

Love,
A very unhappy Seph.

Pluss, the Cowboys didn't make it to the playoffs.  Damn you, Philadelphia Eagles.

You know what I hate?

 

I hate it when people keep opinions bottled up.  If you think I'm annoying, controlling, ugly, or stupid, tell me so!  just say it nicely and I won't bite.  But seriously, I wish everyone was more honest.  instead of not saying something because you're afraid of rocking the boat.  Damnit, if you have an opinion, say so!  If you don't, well, then you're a very bland person. 

 

Honestly, people are so sickeningly polite all the time.  I dislike my teacher strongly, but i have to be nice to her, even when she calls me stupid (indirectly, but still) becaus ethat's the way it has to be.  Now, I'm all for respecting your teachers, but when they call you stupid, I think you should be able to disagree, respectfully.  It's annoying the way people act, as if people are going to hate you if you express your opinion.  In fact, just yesterday, I wished that I could tell you all what I think of you.  but I couldn't because that would be rude.  well, I wasn't sure why I can be rude to Athena, Rachel, and my parents but not y'all, which brings me to another point that I feel is necessary to make.  I have never gotten in a fight with any of y'all.  not even Emily, who I talk to practically every day.  what I've observed is when you argue with someone, your true feelings come out, though they may be jaded by anger, if you scrape that away, you can get an actual opinion.  Like if you take the classic, 'you're a controlling bitch!' you can find that the person thinks you are too dependant and such.  But that is offtopic.  Then again, this whole post is offtopic ranting.  So, just ignore it if you really don't care.  But if you do, I hope you takethe time to tell me what you truely think of me or what your real opinion is.

Thanks.

Your friend

Sephy, who is fed up with the human race right now.

Colleen and I took the one on the right and rode for bout a minute, expecting Rachel to catch up. So, Colleen passed me and I went back to see where Rachel had gone. I didn't see her so, I rode down the left way, figuring she must've gone that way. So, I finally reached her street and Colleen comes ZOOMING up behind me and I'm like "ok, whatever" and look at the houses next to me. Then I look back and she was on the ground, still for a second. Then she started to shake and I thought she was laughing at herself. So, I go over there, grinning and I look over at her and shes' crying. I soon run to find Rachel. When I find her, she's laughing at me for not being able to catch up to her. Then I point to Colleen and Rachel just gets this look like Collen's turned into a bloodsucking creature and runs to go get her dad. So, a day later, I get this Call from Rachel's mom telling me that Colleen was in extensive Care in the hospital. she had gotten a blood vessel in her head broken and was bleeding in her brain. This was because she hadn't buckled her helmet. The thing that really makes me feel guilty is that earlier that day, Rachel and had been complaining about how annoying she and the rest of our friends were, but mostly her. So, the moral of this story is that you should never wear blue underwear on a Wednesday and that you should be careful and think about what could happen to people before you complain. Ok, that's all, you may go now.

Ah, Omaha has been boring, yet interesting.  You see, at my great-grandpa's birthday party-thing, my dad's cousin got proposed to.  Then, also my great-grandpa turned 95 and he has like, no health problems.  Like, he's walking around, talking, sitting, standing, swimming, lifting weights on his own.  obviously, I'm very happy for my second cousin and proud of my great-grandpa.  and then, also, my grandparents are having their 50th anniversary, which is awesome for them.  This trip also consisted of a LOT of hanging around, playing poker, shopping and blah.  not to mention listening to adults mindlessly chatter while my ten year-old cousin ran around with a few of my some-how-distantly-related cousins.  I almost MISS Texas now. :)

Ok, I've decided that, if you want to know so much about my DC/virginia trip, then you should ask me yourself!  But there's one thing in Virginia that was a bit odd.  Ducks.  Right outside of IHOP.  Makes me wonder if that's a regular occurance over there in Virginia.  Heh.  Anyhow, on with my texas tour.

So far, all I've done in Texas is get really really really pissed off at my cousin, which I will explain later for my own amusement, and ride my oddly named horse.  Seriously, who in their right mind names a BLACK horse Sugar? Obviously my cousin isn't one of those.  She named the REDDISH BROWN horse SPICE and the BLACK horse SUGAR!  Ugh!  It's really idiotic.  I should've been able to name one of them, atleast.  It was immature and rude for my stupid cousin to name BOTH horses her names, not to mention naming them based on which one is calmer.  Hmph.  She's a little brat, too.  I let her wear my clothes, use my stuff, I even let her HAVE some of my stuff!  And then she turns around and pulls some stupid stunt like she did a few days ago.  what she did was that I let her wear my personal bathingsuit top and then after she's done with it, she throws the wet bathingsuit on the floor and then later that night, I have to wear a cold bathingsuit because I was being nice!  Another thing she does is she tells the whole fricking neighborhood some bullshit about me supposedly having a crush on this guy across the street, so i flipped her off and i got in a little bit of trouble. Heh, well, you see, the flipping off part was in extreme rage.  What she had done is told everyone in the neighborhood (including the guy) and then she brings the guy in to where i was blissfully ignoring her and playing hearts before i discovered that compuserve exists here, and she says "Katie, (that would be what everyone in the realworld calls me) look who's here."  Obviously, i didn't look, but rather just flipped them off.  Ugh, sometimes she can be sweet, but a lot of times I feel like I should act like a mean, cold-hearted bastard (Hi Athena!).  Because, i let her wear my clothes, i do her hair, I make her houses on the Sims (which she cannot do at all) and then she ignores my authority, bullshits about stuff, and acts like a little inconsiderate brat!  Ugh! Ugh! Ugh!  Can you see my distress?

If you want to know, I am safely in Virginia, and no, she did not eat me, Athena.  Anyhow, I'm reporting from Fredricksburg right now +waves to Eugene, who probably is off doing something cewl right now or actually sleeping for once+;; after just seeing UVA (beautiful campus, I mean absolutely gorgeous!) and Monticello (cewl house!!)  Fredricksburg reinds me of the town my grandparents live in, except Fredricksburg isn't completly full of rednecks, I hope.  As we drove around I saw a lot less cars in the front yard than there are in the little town in Texas.  But, really, the first restaraut I saw was Fatty J's on the Waterfront... that reminded me severly of Texas.  Ah, Texas, I'll be there in 3 days.  For once it's not going to be humid as hell!  Yay!  Which brings up an interesting thought.  What would a t-shirt from Helle, Virginia read?  "I love Helle"?  "I went to Hell and all I got was this stupid t-shirt"?  "Helle is the place to be"?  It's WEIRD!  But, i want to go, none-the-less. :D  Once i have some freetime in Texas, i'll post an account of my days in DC (as if any of y'all care...) but until then, have a nice day and try not to touch the large blue fungus tat has probably grown on your moniter.

Luff,
Seph, who is currently being harrassed by father about her usage of the word "quaint" in reference to Fredricksburg.
